covered: Valid Request: Happy path with required path parameter and multiple valid parameter scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC18).
Empty Response: Tests for empty results when no matches or database is empty (TC04, TC05).
Pagination: Pagination scenarios with offset/limit and multi-page expectations (TC03, TC15).
Query Parameters: Comprehensive testing of valid/invalid query parameters (TC02, TC07, TC08, TC12, TC13, TC14).
Authorization: Tests for missing or invalid authentication tokens (TC09, TC10).
Error Handling: Validation and error responses for invalid inputs and unsupported scenarios (TC06, TC07, TC08, TC11, TC12, TC13).
Regression/Backward Compatibility: Regression tests for empty searchKey and older clients (TC17, TC18).
Integration/Dependency Failures: Tests for dependent service unavailability (TC19).
Accessibility/Payload Structure: Checks on payload shape and accessibility considerations (TC20).
Performance/Load: Large dataset handling and concurrent requests considerations (TC15).
gaps: Rate Limiting: No explicit tests for rate limiting or throttling behavior under high load.
Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or related caching behavior.
Edge Case Permissions: No explicit 403-forbidden scenario in case of insufficient privileges (if applicable).
Internal Server Error coverage: No explicit 500 Internal Server Error scenario (only 503 in system-down case).
URL encoding edge cases: Limited coverage for encoded or special characters in searchKey beyond basic invalid chars.
Unknown/extra query parameter policy: TC14 assumes extra params are ignored; consider validating behavior against policy (ignore vs error).
recommendations: Add rate-limiting/throttling tests to verify stability under bursty traffic and multiple concurrent requests.
Add tests to validate caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and cache invalidation behavior.
Introduce a 403 Forbidden scenario to cover insufficient permission cases, if applicable to the authorization model.
Add a test for 500 Internal Server Error scenarios to cover unexpected server failures beyond 503.
Extend edge-case coverage for URL-encoded or specially formatted searchKey inputs to ensure robust handling.
Clarify and test policy for unknown query parameters (ignore vs error) with explicit tests for both behaviors if policy dictates.
